cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with a search engine prototype. It also involves personalization, which falls under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of constrained bandit optimization suggests that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the paper's focus on de-polarizing content and escaping filter bubbles could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category.
